Package uk.ac.aston.coursework.elevator.objects

Class PersonQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.aston.coursework.elevator.objects.PersonQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Person>
    public class PersonQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Person>
    This class implements Priority Queue using LinkedList. It is restricted so that objects of type Person can enter and use. It uses a field called queueNumber to remember the order of insertion and also, everyone can be accessed and iterated through. The user should use setQueueNumber() method to give a ticket number for each Person. Each type of Person will implement Comparable to decide who has more priority.

    nisat
